steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"f81ui","text":"As soon as possible after sterilization (salpingectomy or tubal ligation), prepare fallopian tube tissue according to the following protocol:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"mii0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"auhn","text":"Human Pregnant Fallopian Tube Tissue Collection and Preservation Methods - UCSD Female Reproductive TMC","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":103}],"data":{}},{"key":"54ki5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3pale","text":"At the time of C-section, prepare uterine endomyometrium tissue according to the following protocol:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"djm4g","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9dlsv","text":"Human Pregnant Uterine Myometrium Tissue Collection and Preservation Methods - UCSD Female Reproductive TMC","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":107}],"data":{}},{"key":"av6a9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cbol8","text":"For this protocol, use tissue that has been snap-frozen.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"4C2BC4B0EDF511EC97938FE01D7A5ED5","url":"http://dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.dm6gpbd5plzp/v1"}},"1":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"E6A1F9D0EDF811EC97938FE01D7A5ED5","url":"http://dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.3byl4bznjvo5/v1"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9ib2j","text":"Isolate nuclei from 4 samples at a time according to the following protocol:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c85t","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"12coq","text":"Nuclei isolation from snap-frozen human placental tissue for bulk ATACseq","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":73}],"data":{}},{"key":"chnpj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"47jl6","text":"Proceed to tagmentation immediately.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6igk","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"effgp","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"03DAB337EDF911EC8EAC0A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.kqdg3p2kel25/v1"}},"1":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"ersqp","text":"Protocol above was written for human placental tissue but can be used for fallopian tube and uterine endomyometrium. Isolated nuclei are paler than those from placenta and should be counted manually with a hemocytometer instead of using an automated cell counter which can struggle to detect them.
